<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="V8" checkit-title="Polynomial and matrix spaces">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <p>
Given the set
<me>\left\{ x^{3} - 2 \, x^{2} + x + 2 , 2 \, x^{2} - 1 , -x^{3} + 3 \, x^{2} + 3 \, x - 2 , x^{3} - 6 \, x^{2} + 9 \, x + 5 \right\}</me>
write a statement involving a 

polynomial
equation that's equivalent to each claim below.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>
                        <p>
The set of 

polynomials
is linearly <em>independent</em>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>
The set of 

polynomials
is linearly <em>dependent</em>.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>
Explain how to determine which of these statements is true.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            <me>
\mathrm{RREF}\, \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
2 &amp; -1 &amp; -2 &amp; 5 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 &amp; 9 \\
-2 &amp; 2 &amp; 3 &amp; -6 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -1 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] = \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]
            </me>
        </p>
        <p>
The set
    is linearly 
    
    <em>dependent</em>.
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
